question: Describe all the CDS located in region 8 of the genome NBC_01571.
label: Test
answer_sql_expected: SELECT   cds.*,   r.*,   g.* FROM   antismash.regions r   JOIN antismash.dna_sequences d ON r.accession = d.accession   JOIN antismash.genomes g ON d.genome_id = g.genome_id   JOIN antismash.cdss cds ON r.region_id = cds.region_id WHERE   g.assembly_id = 'NBC_01571'   AND r.region_number = 8;
answer_sql_LLM:
SELECT 
    cds.* 
FROM 
    antismash.cdss cds
    JOIN antismash.regions r ON cds.region_id = r.region_id
    JOIN antismash.dna_sequences ds ON r.accession = ds.accession
    JOIN antismash.genomes g ON ds.genome_id = g.genome_id
WHERE 
    g.assembly_id = 'NBC_01571'
    AND r.region_number = 8;
answer_summary_LLM: Region 8 of the genome NBC_01571 contains 47 CDSs with various proteins, including elongation factor Tu, VTT domain-containing protein, thiolase family protein, helix-turn-helix transcriptional regulator, cupin, PmoA family protein, Gfo/Idh/MocA family oxidoreductase, undecaprenyl-diphosphate phosphatase, hypothetical proteins, MazG-like family protein, transposase family proteins, phytanoyl-CoA dioxygenase family protein, methionine adenosyltransferase, crotonyl-CoA carboxylase/reductase, DUF3037 domain-containing protein, cytochrome P450, TetR/AcrR family transcriptional regulator, MFS transporter, DUF6204 family protein, DUF2087 domain-containing protein, acyltransferase domain-containing protein, methyltransferase domain-containing protein, aspartate 1-decarboxylase, ACP S-malonyltransferase (fabD), amino acid adenylation domain-containing proteins, SDR family NAD(P)-dependent oxidoreductases, L-histidine N(alpha)-methyltransferase, KR domain-containing protein, 4'-phosphopantetheinyl transferase superfamily protein, ISAzo13 family transposase, group II intron reverse transcriptase/maturase, and several other hypothetical proteins.
